    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6b753501_9f126464",
        "filename": "machine-db/appengine/config/config_test.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 34,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-15T01:03:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "you can move this into a helper function to reduce LOC\n\nrunValidation :\u003d func(dc []*config.DatacenterConfig) error {\n  c :\u003d \u0026validation.Context{}\n  validateDatacenters(c, dc)\n  return c.Finalize()\n}\n\n....\n\nSo(runValidation([]*config.DatacenterConfig{\n  ...\n}, ShouldErrLike, \"....\")\n\nNote also that an error returned by validation is actually a list of errors (https://chromium.googlesource.com/infra/luci/luci-go/+/master/common/config/validation/validation.go#29) and you can extract them and assert them in tests individually, if simpler.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 31,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 34,
        "endChar": 25
      },
      "revId": "0c3216a5456862ca554fc93727cfbcd08f08c6f3",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f8151184_64da39d8",
        "filename": "machine-db/appengine/config/config_test.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 34,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-15T02:43:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I prefer tests to be verbose, even when lines are duplicated, so you can look at any one failing test in isolation and figure out what it\u0027s trying to assert without having to jump around in the file. I realize in this case you only have to look in one extra place, but do you mind if I don\u0027t create a helper function?",
      "parentUuid": "6b753501_9f126464",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 31,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 34,
        "endChar": 25
      },
      "revId": "0c3216a5456862ca554fc93727cfbcd08f08c6f3",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
